Azure Repos is the place in Azure DevOps where your team stores and manages code.

What is it?

Azure Repos is a code storage and version control tool.

That means it helps you:
  
  Save your code
  
  Track changes over time
  
  Work with teammates
  
  Go back to older versions if something breaks


If you are new and there is a coding folder then we use Clone the Repo

  Cloning means downloading a copy of the project from Azure Repos onto your computer

We use the git clone <repo-url> comman

  git clone https://dev.azure.com/company/project/_git/repo-name


To make a branch you will use this:

  git checkout -b feature/map-sidebar


To Upload your branch from your computer to Azure Repos

  git push origin <branch-name>


Before you start coding, update your project so you have the newest team changes.

  git checkout main                          Go to the main branch
  
  git pull origin main                       Download the newest code
  
  git checkout -b feature/my-task            Create a new branch for your work

  git branch -d old-branch-name              Once you are sure delete the old branch

Sometime there will be conflicting merging issues. A merge conflict happens when, You and someone else changed the same part of the same file.

You fix the file manually, then:

  git add .

  git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict"













